      "code": "Total = C(n,3) - bad\n\nFor a bad triple: at least two problems share a topic, and at least two problems share a difficulty.\n\nCases for bad triple:\n1. All three share same topic (then at least two share topic), and at least two share difficulty\n2. Exactly two share same topic, and at least two share difficulty\n\nActually let me think differently. \n\nA triple is bad iff: there exist two problems with same topic AND there exist two problems (possibly different pair) with same difficulty.\n\nLet me count bad triples directly.\n\nFor each pair (i,j) with same topic: they form a bad triple with k if k also shares a topic with i or j OR k shares a difficulty with i or j... No this gets complicated.\n\nAlternative: count triples where NOT all topics distinct AND NOT all difficulties distinct.\n\nLet cnt_a[x] = number of problems with topic x, cnt_b[y] = number of problems with difficulty y.\n\nBad triples: triples where \u2203 repeated topic AND \u2203 repeated difficulty.\n\nLet me use: bad = (triples with repeated topic) + (triples with repeated difficulty) - (triples with repeated topic OR repeated difficulty)... no that's wrong direction.\n\nbad = triples with (repeated topic AND repeated difficulty)\n= total - triples with (all topics distinct OR all difficulties distinct)... no.\n\nBy inclusion-exclusion:\n|A \u2229 B| = total - |A^c| - |B^c| + |A^c \u2229 B^c|\n\nwhere A = \"repeated topic exists\", B = \"repeated difficulty exists\"\nA^c = all topics distinct, B^c = all difficulties distinct\n\n|A \u2229 B| = total - |A^c \u222a B^c|... no.\n\n|A \u2229 B| = total - |A^c| - |B^c| + |A^c \u2229 B^c|\n\nWe want answer = total - |A \u2229 B| = |A^c| + |B^c| - |A^c \u2229 B^c|\n\nSo: answer = (triples with all topics distinct) + (triples with all difficulties distinct) - (triples with all topics distinct AND all difficulties distinct)\n\nNow I need to count triples where all topics AND all difficulties are distinct.\n\nTotal triples with all topics distinct: C(n,3) - sum over x of C(cnt_a[x], 2)*(n - cnt_a[x]) - sum over x of C(cnt_a[x],3)... \n\nActually: triples with NOT all topics distinct = sum_x C(cnt_a[x],2)*(n-cnt_a[x]) + sum_x C(cnt_a[x],3)... no.\n\nTriples with at least two sharing topic = sum_x [C(cnt_a[x],2)*(n - cnt_a[x]) + C(cnt_a[x],3)]\n\nSo triples with all topics distinct = C(n,3) - sum_x [C(cnt_a[x],2)*(n-cnt_a[x]) + C(cnt_a[x],3)]\n\nSimilarly for difficulties.\n\nFor triples with all topics AND all difficulties distinct: this is harder. \n\nall_distinct = C(n,3) - (not all topics distinct) - (not all difficulties distinct) + (not all topics distinct AND not all difficulties distinct)\n\nSo all_distinct = C(n,3) - bad_topic - bad_diff + bad_both\n\nwhere bad_both = |A \u2229 B| which is what we're trying to compute... circular.\n\nLet me just compute: answer = all_topic_distinct + all_diff_distinct - all_both_distinct\n\nall_both_distinct = C(n,3) - bad_topic - bad_diff + bad_both\n\nSo answer = all_topic + all_diff - C(n,3) + bad_topic + bad_diff - bad_both\n\n= (C(n,3) - bad_topic) + (C(n,3) - bad_diff) - C(n,3) + bad_topic + bad_diff - bad_both\n\n= C(n,3) - bad_both\n\nWhich confirms answer = total - bad_both. So I need to count bad_both directly.\n\nBad triple: at least 2 share topic AND at least 2 share difficulty. For each pair sharing a topic (i,j), count k such that k shares difficulty with i or j. But avoid double counting.\n\nimport sys\nfrom collections import defaultdict\ninput=sys.stdin.readline\n\ndef solve():\n    n=int(input())\n    a=[]; b=[]\n    topic=defaultdict(list); diff=defaultdict(list)\n    for i in range(n):\n        x,y=map(int,input().split())\n        a.append(x); b.append(y)\n        topic[x].append(i); diff[y].append(i)\n    total=n*(n-1)*(n-2)//6\n    # count bad triples\n    # For each pair with same topic, count third problem sharing difficulty with either\n    bad=0\n    diff_set=defaultdict(set)\n    for i in range(n): diff_set[b[i]].add(i)\n    # pair (i,j) same topic: bad if exists k sharing diff with i or j\n    # |share_diff_with_i or share_diff_with_j| = |cnt_b[b[i]]-1| + |cnt_b[b[j]]-1| - |share with both| - overlap\n    cnt_b=defaultdict(int)\n    for x in b: cnt_b[x]+=1\n    cnt_a=defaultdict(int)\n    for x in a: cnt_a[x]+=1\n    \n    for x,lst in topic.items():\n        m=len(lst)\n        if m<2: continue\n        for ii in range(len(lst)):\n            for jj in range(ii+1,len(lst)):\n                i,j=lst[ii],lst[jj]\n                bi,bj=b[i],b[j]\n                # count k not in {i,j} with b[k]==bi or b[k]==bj\n                if bi==bj:\n                    cnt=cnt_b[bi]-2\n                else:\n                    cnt=(cnt_b[bi]-1)+(cnt_b[bj]-1)\n                bad+=cnt\n    \n    print(total-bad)\n\nt=int(input())\nfor _ in range(t): solve()",
